EVAN RICH: Uh-huh.

00:38:26.190 --> 00:38:27.690
AUDIENCE: I'm really
curious how you

00:38:27.690 --> 00:38:29.240
do that with Brussels sprouts.

00:38:29.240 --> 00:38:29.990
It's hard to get--

00:38:29.990 --> 00:38:32.850
I mean, do you get really
young Brussels sprouts then?

00:38:32.850 --> 00:38:35.350
EVAN RICH: I mean, you can get
just regular Brussels sprouts

00:38:35.350 --> 00:38:37.220
and do it the same way.

00:38:37.220 --> 00:38:40.750
There's a great farmer at the
market called [INAUDIBLE],,

00:38:40.750 --> 00:38:42.130
and they have Brussels sprouts.

00:38:42.130 --> 00:38:44.740
And they're big, they
seem almost bigger

00:38:44.740 --> 00:38:47.290
than you would think
Brussels sprouts should be.

00:38:47.290 --> 00:38:50.020
And if you blanch them
real quick and just sear

00:38:50.020 --> 00:38:52.360
them just like that,
maybe take the whole thing

00:38:52.360 --> 00:38:55.924
and cut them in half and blanch
them and then sear them--

00:38:55.924 --> 00:38:57.340
actually in the
cookbook, there is

00:38:57.340 --> 00:38:59.200
a recipe for a
Brussels sprout Caesar

00:38:59.200 --> 00:39:00.460
that we do at the restaurant.

00:39:00.460 --> 00:39:03.190
And we just take Brussels
sprouts, cut them in half,

00:39:03.190 --> 00:39:05.830
and then put them in a
pan with the face down

00:39:05.830 --> 00:39:07.120
and slow cook them.

00:39:07.120 --> 00:39:11.370
And we put a lid on it to
help get everything going,

00:39:11.370 --> 00:39:13.660
and the sweetness
comes out really well.

00:39:13.660 --> 00:39:17.170
SARAH RICH: Also to create a
lot of that caramelization,

00:39:17.170 --> 00:39:18.980
getting a lot more surface area.

00:39:18.980 --> 00:39:21.940
So if you just take the Brussels
sprout and you can shave it,

00:39:21.940 --> 00:39:25.270
you can use a mandolin, just
like the mandolin like this

00:39:25.270 --> 00:39:25.990
to shave it.

00:39:25.990 --> 00:39:28.490
Or you can cut it
up really thinly,

00:39:28.490 --> 00:39:30.100
and then you have
a lot more that you

00:39:30.100 --> 00:39:32.470
can get touching the pan
that you can caramelize it.

00:39:32.470 --> 00:39:33.970
I do that sometimes,
that works too.

00:39:33.970 --> 00:39:34.962
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:39:34.962 --> 00:39:36.624
SARAH RICH: Mm-hmm.

00:39:36.624 --> 00:39:37.790
SPEAKER 1: Again, fire away.

